The paper deals with the problem of adaptive consensus control of nonlinear multi-agent systems, which involves topics related to control systems (cs.SY), multi-agent systems (cs.MA), robotics (cs.RO), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper proposes a novel variable transformation for decoupled consensus control design, which is a significant contribution to the field of cooperative control and multi-agent systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SY, followed by cs.MA, cs.RO, cs.AI, and cs.LG.
